==Scots Gaelic==

===Noun===
'''b&ugrave;ird'''

# A [[table]] (genitive form)

===Related terms===
*[[bord]] (nominative form of 'b&ugrave;ird')

===References===
'b&ugrave;ird' is the genitive singular or nominative plural form of 'b&ograve;rd' meaning 'table'.  After the definite article it changes to 'bh&ugrave;ird' as in 'Beinn a Bh&ugrave;ird' - 'The table mountain'.

Malcolm Maclennan - A pronouncing and etymological dictionary of the Gaelic language - published jointly by Acair and Aberdeen University Press.